main event: Mr. and Mrs. Carl A. Schlieckert observed a hovering object in Wapello, Iowa on March 22, 1967.
interesting points: The object was initially thought to be an aircraft but emitted no lights and was silent., The witnesses observed the object for 15 minutes without it moving., The witnesses could not estimate the size or altitude of the object., No aircraft were reported in the area at the time of the sighting., The object showed no physical evidence.
witness description: Mr. and Mrs. Carl A. Schlieckert, reliable witnesses
